
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #f0f0f0

' Define classes
class Hospital {
    +String name
    +List<ExaminationType> allowedExaminationTypes
    +applyPermission(ExaminationType type)
}

class ExaminationType {
    +String name
    +boolean isAllowedBy(Hospital hospital)
}

class Doctor {
    +String name
    +Hospital hospital
}

class Patient {
    +String name
    +String problem
}

class Problem {
    +String name
    +List<TreatmentPlan> treatmentPlans
}

class TreatmentPlan {
    +String name
    +List<ExaminationType> recommendedExaminations
}

class ActualTreatment {
    +Patient patient
    +Doctor doctor
    +List<Examination> examinations
    +List<MedicalAction> medicalActions
}

class Examination {
    +ExaminationType type
    +Hospital hospital
    +Patient patient
}

class MedicalAction {
    +String description
}

' Associations
Hospital "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : allows
Hospital "1" -- "1" Doctor : employs
Doctor "1" -- "1" Patient : treats
Patient "1" -- "1" Problem : has
Problem "1" -- "1" TreatmentPlan : defines
TreatmentPlan "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : recommends
Doctor "1" -- "1" ActualTreatment : creates
ActualTreatment "1" -- "0..*" Examination : includes
ActualTreatment "1" -- "0..*" MedicalAction : includes
Examination "1" -- "1" Hospital : performed at
Examination "1" -- "1" Patient : for

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **Hospital**: Manages allowed examination types and can apply for permission to perform certain types.
- **ExaminationType**: Represents a type of examination (e.g., "echography", "radiology").
- **Doctor**: Belongs to a hospital and diagnoses patients.
- **Patient**: Has a specific problem and receives an actual treatment.
- **Problem**: Is associated with one or more treatment plans.
- **TreatmentPlan**: Defines the recommended examinations for a particular problem.
- **ActualTreatment**: Includes both the recommended examinations and any freely chosen medical actions.
- **Examination**: A specific instance of an examination, which must be performed at a hospital that has the necessary permissions.
- **MedicalAction**: Represents any medical action not covered by the recommended examinations.

